You have to keep track of multiple points and many moving pieces. Fun game to focus on.

replyContent:
Hello. Thank you for your comment! 
No, Traffix doesn't have achievements. The Google Play Games button allows you to stay connected to your account and save your progress. Thank you.

replyContent:
Hello Trevor! Thank you for reporting the issue.
We had a little problem with the latest version. The level order was randomized and that did affect the progress storage. We have been working on extra content and we will add new levels in the next update. We are very excited about the improvements we've made! Please, stay tuned!

Quick Summary, You know you have found an excellent game when just the start screen is appealing. The controls are amazing and the sounds are perfectly satisfying. Its always a rush when you get the cars extremely close to each other and it doesn't hit. Lastly, Shout out to the Verge for sending me here. 10/10 Would recommend. Well done!

Its beautiful, and challenging, I would prefer an easier mode where I control all the car lanes and only the trains/trams were not stoppable by the user. Or like a zen mode where its more just fun and not so difficult.

Easy to understand with possible real life implications. This is what traffic signals need to do in order to balance the traffic flow! The only difference is that in this game, the player must manually control each signal. The user interface is clean and elegant. The control are easy to understand. It's all very easy to use and play!
